'''su''' is the ''substitute user'' command.  it can be used to impersonate other users on the linux computer.  it is a part of the gnu coreutils package.

''su -c <command>'' will run commands as root by default (unless a different user is specified as documented in the '''su(1)''' manual page).

{{Cmd|su -c 'shutdown -h now'}}

''su -c <user> $USER'' will impersonate and run commands as $USER

